bisyncConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Bisync port.

bisyncConfigPortIndex.name: bisyncConfigPortIndex
bisyncConfigPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this port. Current supported Bisync numbers are 1-4.

bisyncConfigType.name: bisyncConfigType
bisyncConfigType.description: The port type. TBSC (Terminal Bisync) ports emulate a Host and polls the downstream controllers). HBSC ports (Host Bisync) ports emulate a line with Terminal Controllers (CUs) and respond to polls from the Host.

bisyncNAUName.name: bisyncNAUName
bisyncNAUName.description: The NAU name of this port. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

bisyncInitState.name: bisyncInitState
bisyncInitState.description: The initial state of the Bisync port. If configured for 'in-service', then the Bisync port will be brougt up automattically when the unit is powered up. If configured for 'out-of-service', then the Bisync port must be manually enabled by operator intervention (i.e. enable command must be sent). The default value is 'enabled'.

bisyncCarrier.name: bisyncCarrier
bisyncCarrier.description: This field indicates whether Carrier (a.k.a. CD or DCD, RS-232 pin 8) is constant or switched for DCE devices (internally clocked), or Request To Send (a.k.a. RTS, RS-232 pin 4) is constant or switched. The default value for this parameter is 'constant'.

bisyncClocking.name: bisyncClocking
bisyncClocking.description: Clocking source for this port. Setting 'internal' will cause the port to emulate a physical DCE, and setting external will cause the port to emulate a physical DTE. X21 External and Internal are used (with the proper external adapter) to support X.21 Leased Line operation for RS-422/RS-530 (25 pin balanced) interfaces. X21 operation is not supported for boards that operate RS-232 or V.35. The default value for this field is 'external'.

bisyncSpeed.name: bisyncSpeed
bisyncSpeed.description: The ports speed in bits per second. The default value is 9600 bits per second. Speeds higher than 64000 are not supported.

bisyncPause.name: bisyncPause
bisyncPause.description: This parameter defines the amount of time between polls in 1/100 second (10 millisecond) intervals. If set to zero then the port will poll the CUs as fast as possible. The minimum value for this parameter is 5 and the timer has a resolution of 25 milliseconds. The default value is 20 (.20 seconds). This field is not applicable to a Host port. It returns a dummy value.

bisyncReplyTimer.name: bisyncReplyTimer
bisyncReplyTimer.description: The time to wait for a response in seconds. The default value for this field is 3 seconds.

bisyncRetries.name: bisyncRetries
bisyncRetries.description: The maximum number of retries (N2 value) before failing a CU. The default value for this field is 5.

bisyncSlowpollTimer.name: bisyncSlowpollTimer
bisyncSlowpollTimer.description: The time to wait in seconds before attempting a slowpoll. The default value for this field is 30 seconds.

bisyncSessTerm.name: bisyncSessTerm
bisyncSessTerm.description: The type of session termination used. Only applies to Host BSC ports.

bisyncIBS.name: bisyncIBS
bisyncIBS.description: Some of non IBM 3270 BSC controllers can not handle ESC character but IBM 3270 BSC implementation requires ESC character. A new configuration parameter for Terminal BSC line as described below The default value is Yes.

bisyncCTS.name: bisyncCTS
bisyncCTS.description: Defines whether CTS is an input signal used to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

bisyncDCD.name: bisyncDCD
bisyncDCD.description: Defines whether DCD is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncDSR.name: bisyncDSR
bisyncDSR.description: Defines whether DSR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DSR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncDTR.name: bisyncDTR
bisyncDTR.description: Defines whether DTR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and DTR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncRTS.name: bisyncRTS
bisyncRTS.description: Defines whether RTS is an input signal to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and RTS is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

bisyncReturnClock.name: bisyncReturnClock
bisyncReturnClock.description: Defines whether Return Clock (SCTE) is available as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncStatsEntry.name: bisyncStatsEntry
bisyncStatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Bisync port.

bisyncStatsPortIndex.name: bisyncStatsPortIndex
bisyncStatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this Bisync port. Current supported numbers are 1-4.

bisyncPortType.name: bisyncPortType
bisyncPortType.description: The port type. TBSC (Terminal Bisync) ports emulate a Host and poll the downstream controllers). HBSC ports (Host Bisync) ports emulate a line with Terminal Controllers (PUs) and respond to polls from the Host or upstream PU.

bisyncCRCErrors.name: bisyncCRCErrors
bisyncCRCErrors.description: The number of receive frame CRC errors.

frameRelayConfigTable.name: frameRelayConfigTable
frameRelayConfigTable.description: A table of Sync product Frame Relay information.

frameRelayConfigEntry.name: frameRelayConfigEntry
frameRelayConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Sync product Frame Relay port.

frameRelayConfigPortIndex.name: frameRelayConfigPortIndex
frameRelayConfigPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this port.

frameRelayInitState.name: frameRelayInitState
frameRelayInitState.description: The initial state of the Frame Relay port. If configured for 'in-service', then the Frame Relay port will be brougt up automatically when the unit is powered up. If configured for 'out-of-service', then the Frame Relay port must be manually enabled by operator intervention (i.e. enable command must be sent). The default value is 'enabled'.

frameRelayClocking.name: frameRelayClocking
frameRelayClocking.description: Clocking source for this port. Setting 'internal' will cause the port to emulate a physical DCE, and setting external will cause the port to emulate a physical DTE. X21 External and Internal are used (with the proper external adapter) to support X.21 Leased Line operation for RS-422/RS-530 (25 pin balanced) interfaces. X21 operation is not supported for boards that operate RS-232 or V.35. The default value for this field is 'external'.

frameRelaySpeed.name: frameRelaySpeed
frameRelaySpeed.description: The ports speed in bits per second. The default value is 9600 bits per second. Speeds higher than 19200 are not supported on RS-232 port Sync products (must be V.35 or RS-422).

frameRelayLocalManagementProtocol.name: frameRelayLocalManagementProtocol
frameRelayLocalManagementProtocol.description: The ports management protocol type. Annex D = ANSI T1.617 Annex D LMI = Frame Relay Manufacturers LMI The default value is Annex D.

frameRelayLinkPollingTimer.name: frameRelayLinkPollingTimer
frameRelayLinkPollingTimer.description: Measured in seconds, intervals of 5 T391 - Annex D nT1 - LMI The default value for this field is 5 seconds.

frameRelayFullStatusPollingCount.name: frameRelayFullStatusPollingCount
frameRelayFullStatusPollingCount.description: The number of polls that a full status poll is issued. N391 - Annex D nT1 - LMI The default value for this field is 6.

frameRelayT1Timer.name: frameRelayT1Timer
frameRelayT1Timer.description: The default LLC T1 timer value in seconds. T1 should be greater than T2 and less than Ti. Currently supported values are 1 to 25 seconds. The default value for this field is 3 seconds.

frameRelayT2Timer.name: frameRelayT2Timer
frameRelayT2Timer.description: The default LLC T2 timer value in tenths of seconds. If configured for 0 then the T2 timer is disabled and an RR frame will be sent for every I frame received. Current supported values are 0 and 2-50. T2 should be less than T1. The default value for this field is 0 (disabled).

frameRelayTiTimer.name: frameRelayTiTimer
frameRelayTiTimer.description: The default LLC Ti (inactivity) timer value in seconds. Ti should be greater than T1. Currently supported values are 2 to 50 seconds. The default value for this field is 30 seconds.

frameRelayRxWindowSize.name: frameRelayRxWindowSize
frameRelayRxWindowSize.description: The default LLC receive window (N3) size. Note that this is not the same receive window as defined in IEEE 802.2 LLC. This is N3 which is the number of I frames received before an RR frame is sent (defined as N3 in IEEE 802.2 LLC). Current allowable values are 1-7. The default value for this field is 7.

frameRelayTxWindowSize.name: frameRelayTxWindowSize
frameRelayTxWindowSize.description: The defalut LLC transmit window size. Current allowable values are 1-7. The default value for this field is 7.

frameRelayMaxRetries.name: frameRelayMaxRetries
frameRelayMaxRetries.description: The default LLC maximum number of retries (N2 value). The default value for this field is 15.

frameRelayNAUName.name: frameRelayNAUName
frameRelayNAUName.description: The NAU name of this port. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

frameRelayVirtualMACAddress.name: frameRelayVirtualMACAddress
frameRelayVirtualMACAddress.description: The F/R WAN is treated as a token ring. This address is used for communication with other bridges in the network.

frameRelayVirtualRingNumber.name: frameRelayVirtualRingNumber
frameRelayVirtualRingNumber.description: The F/R WAN is treated as a token ring. This is the ring number for the F/R network to which the port is attached. It must be a unique ring number in the network. This value is configured in hex from 0 to FFF. The default value for this field is 1.

frameRelayVirtualBridgeNumber.name: frameRelayVirtualBridgeNumber
frameRelayVirtualBridgeNumber.description: The F/R WAN is treated as a token ring. This variable only has significance if more than 1 F/R port is configured. The default value for this field is 1.

frameRelayIPAddress.name: frameRelayIPAddress
frameRelayIPAddress.description: This is the IP Address of this interface.

frameRelayNetworkMask.name: frameRelayNetworkMask
frameRelayNetworkMask.description: This is the network mask to be used on this interface.

frameRelayDefaultGatewayAddress.name: frameRelayDefaultGatewayAddress
frameRelayDefaultGatewayAddress.description: Default gateway address to be used when sending responses on this interface.

frameRelaySessSwitchThreshold.name: frameRelaySessSwitchThreshold
frameRelaySessSwitchThreshold.description: Describes the session switch threshold for a session to switch between eVR and pVR. The value represents the LLC time-out occurrence for any session on this port. If one session has the configured number of time-outs, all sessions using that PVC are switched between eVR and pVR. Sessions that do not have a pVR are terminated.

frameRelaySwitchedBackup.name: frameRelaySwitchedBackup
frameRelaySwitchedBackup.description: Defines the switched backup protocol used for dial backup. The range of this parameter is NONE or RACAL DTR-initiated. The default value is NONE.

frameRelaySwitchedLineWaitTimer.name: frameRelaySwitchedLineWaitTimer
frameRelaySwitchedLineWaitTimer.description: This parameter defines the maximum amount of time the FrameNode waits for the DAP to establish a dial connection before switching back to the dedicated line. This parameter is required because the DAP does not notify the FrameNode as to whether the dial backup connection was successful or not. This parameter, in concert with a high level protocol, helps determine whether or not the connection was successful. This parameter is expressed in minutes. The range of this parameter is from 1 minute to 60 minutes. The default value is 5 minutes.

frameRelayDedLineWaitTimer.name: frameRelayDedLineWaitTimer
frameRelayDedLineWaitTimer.description: The FCC regulation for Autodialers requires that an Autodialer waits between successive dial operations. This parameter satisfies the FCC requirements. It controls the maximum time the FrameNode waits before initiating another dial restoral operation if the previous operation fails. The timer starts when DTR is lowered. DTR is raised again upon expiration of the timer. This parameter is expressed in minutes. Its range is from 10 minutes to 120 minutes with a one minute resolution. The default value it 10 minutes.

frameRelayCommittedBurst.name: frameRelayCommittedBurst
frameRelayCommittedBurst.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of bits, during time interval Tc, the network agrees to accept under normal conditions. This parameter must match the configured value for the network. The value of this parameter can not be greater that the line speed. The range of the parameter is 1Kbits to 2048Kbits. The default value equals the line speed. However, this value depends on the Measurement Period Tc and the line speed. The value is expressed in Kbits.

frameRelayExcessBurst.name: frameRelayExcessBurst
frameRelayExcessBurst.description: This is the maximum number of uncommitted bits, during time interval Tc, the network accepts above the committed burst size Bc. When the Excess burst Governor is configured to YES, the FrameNode tries to limit the throughput to the Bc + Be bits in the Time Period Tc. The default value of this parameter is 0. The range is from 0K to 2048K. However, the value depends on the Measurement Period Tc and the speed of the line. The value is expressed in Kbits.

frameRelayBridgingProtocol.name: frameRelayBridgingProtocol
frameRelayBridgingProtocol.description: This parameter specifies the bridging protocol to be used over Frame Relay link. This parameter has no effect if bridging is not turned on. The range of this parameter is SRB (source route bridging), TBR(transparent bridging) or BOTH. The value is BOTH.

frameRelayProxyARP.name: frameRelayProxyARP
frameRelayProxyARP.description: This parameter defines whether PROXY ARP is enabled for F/R attached devices or not. Range of this parameter is ENABLED or DISABLED. The value is 'DISABLED'.

frameRelaySecondDefaultGatewayAddress.name: frameRelaySecondDefaultGatewayAddress
frameRelaySecondDefaultGatewayAddress.description: Second Default gateway address to be used when sending responses on this interface.

frameRelayAlternateIPAddress.name: frameRelayAlternateIPAddress
frameRelayAlternateIPAddress.description: This is the Alternate IP Address for single port dial up connection.

frameRelayAlternateNetmask.name: frameRelayAlternateNetmask
frameRelayAlternateNetmask.description: This is the Alternate network mask for IP for single port dial up connecton.

frameRelayLLC2FrameFormat.name: frameRelayLLC2FrameFormat
frameRelayLLC2FrameFormat.description: This parameter specifies the LLC2 frame format to be used over Frame Relay link. The range of this parameter is Token Ring, Ethernet Version 2, IEEE 802.3 or ALL. The value is ALL.

frameRelayMultiflagSeparation.name: frameRelayMultiflagSeparation
frameRelayMultiflagSeparation.description: This parameter specifies whether the unit will insert more than one flag between frames. The range of this parameter is yes and no. The value is 'no'.

frameRelayRestrictTerminateSessUsage.name: frameRelayRestrictTerminateSessUsage
frameRelayRestrictTerminateSessUsage.description: This parameter specifies whether terminated sessions are to follow spanning tree states or not over Frame Relay Link. The range of this parameter is No and SpanningTree. The value is 'no'.

frameRelayRIPUpdtTimer.name: frameRelayRIPUpdtTimer
frameRelayRIPUpdtTimer.description: Defines frequency at which the RIP packets are sent over this interface. The range of this parameter is from 10 seconds to 180 seconds. A value of 0 implies no RIP is sent over this interface. Default value is 60 seconds

frameRelayRIPAge.name: frameRelayRIPAge
frameRelayRIPAge.description: Defines frequency at which the learned RIP entries are removed if not corresponding RIP update is received. The range of this parameter is from 40 seconds to 540 seconds. Default value is 180 seconds

frameRelaySAPUpdtTimer.name: frameRelaySAPUpdtTimer
frameRelaySAPUpdtTimer.description: Defines frequency at which the SAP packets are sent over this interface. The range of this parameter is from 10 seconds to 180 seconds. A value of 0 implies that no SAP broadcasts are sent over this interface. Default value is 60 seconds

frameRelaySAPAge.name: frameRelaySAPAge
frameRelaySAPAge.description: Defines frequency at which the learned SAP entries are removed if not corresponding SAP update is received. The range of this parameter is from 40 seconds to 720 seconds. Default value is 180 seconds

frameRelayRSM.name: frameRelayRSM
frameRelayRSM.description: The Routing Summary Information parameter indicates whether the routing summary information should be generated in the RIP on that interface. If RSM is set to NO, RIP will broadcast subnet information as it is defined in the routing table. Default value is 'NO'

frameRelayARP.name: frameRelayARP
frameRelayARP.description: The ARP parameter indicates what format of ARP should be generated. Default value is 'Auto'

frameRelayCTS.name: frameRelayCTS
frameRelayCTS.description: Defines whether CTS is an input signal used to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

frameRelayDCD.name: frameRelayDCD
frameRelayDCD.description: Defines whether DCD is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

frameRelayDSR.name: frameRelayDSR
frameRelayDSR.description: Defines whether DSR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DSR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

frameRelayDTR.name: frameRelayDTR
frameRelayDTR.description: Defines whether DTR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and DTR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

frameRelayRTS.name: frameRelayRTS
frameRelayRTS.description: Defines whether RTS is an input signal to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and RTS is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

frameRelayReturnClock.name: frameRelayReturnClock
frameRelayReturnClock.description: Defines whether Return Clock (SCTE) is available as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

frameRelayStatsTable.name: frameRelayStatsTable
frameRelayStatsTable.description: A table of Frame Relay information.

frameRelayStatsEntry.name: frameRelayStatsEntry
frameRelayStatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Frame Relay port.

frameRelayStatsPortIndex.name: frameRelayStatsPortIndex
frameRelayStatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this Frame Relay port.

frameRelayInOctets.name: frameRelayInOctets
frameRelayInOctets.description: The number of bytes received inclusive of all valid bytes in the frame relay frame except for the CRC field (frame relay header included).

frameRelayOutOctets.name: frameRelayOutOctets
frameRelayOutOctets.description: The number of bytes transmitted inclusive of all bytes in the frame relay frame except for the CRC field (frame relay header included).

frameRelaySampleDuration.name: frameRelaySampleDuration
frameRelaySampleDuration.description: The sample duration in seconds for Frame Relay Statistics for this port.

frameRelayCRCErrors.name: frameRelayCRCErrors
frameRelayCRCErrors.description: The number of received CRC errors.

frameRelayRecvAborts.name: frameRelayRecvAborts
frameRelayRecvAborts.description: The number of received frame aborts received.

frameRelayTxDe.name: frameRelayTxDe
frameRelayTxDe.description: Total number of frames sent with the DE bit.

frameRelayRxDe.name: frameRelayRxDe
frameRelayRxDe.description: Total number of frames received with the DE bit.

frameRelaySwitchedAttempts.name: frameRelaySwitchedAttempts
frameRelaySwitchedAttempts.description: The total number of times a switched backup is attempted.

frameRelaySwitchedAttemptsSuccessful.name: frameRelaySwitchedAttemptsSuccessful
frameRelaySwitchedAttemptsSuccessful.description: The total number of times switched backup attempts were successful.

frExtCircuitTable.name: frExtCircuitTable
frExtCircuitTable.description: A table containing information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding virtual circuits.

frExtCircuitEntry.name: frExtCircuitEntry
frExtCircuitEntry.description: The information regarding a single Data Link Connection Identifier.

frExtCircuitIfIndex.name: frExtCircuitIfIndex
frExtCircuitIfIndex.description: The ifIndex Value of the ifEntry this virtual circuit is layered onto.

frExtCircuitDlci.name: frExtCircuitDlci
frExtCircuitDlci.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.6
frExtCircuitDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this virtual circuit.

frExtCircuitStatusIgnored.name: frExtCircuitStatusIgnored
frExtCircuitStatusIgnored.description: This field is used for consolidating status of the unit. The status of this circuit is not put into consideration when consolidating status of the unit if this field is set to yes.

frExtCircuitStatusAcknowledged.name: frExtCircuitStatusAcknowledged
frExtCircuitStatusAcknowledged.description: This field is used for consolidating status of the unit. When this field is set to acknowledge, unit will re-consolidate its status without putting the status of this circuit into consideration. Subseqent status change of the circuit will cause the unit to include it in computing the status of the unit. Setting this value to no has no effect.

frExtCircuitPartnerId.name: frExtCircuitPartnerId
frExtCircuitPartnerId.description: This is the unit id of the FrameNode at the other end of the Frame relay PVC. It consists of a 1 to 8 octets right justified case-sensitive ASCII field which uniquely identifies the unit. If the unit at the other end of the Frame Relay PVC is not a Sync Research FrameNode, or and OEM equipment NON-FN is returned for this object.

frExtCircuitTxDe.name: frExtCircuitTxDe
frExtCircuitTxDe.description: Total number of frames sent with DE bit for this PVC.

frExtCircuitRxDe.name: frExtCircuitRxDe
frExtCircuitRxDe.description: Total number of frames received with the DE bit for this PVC.

frExtCircuitMinBits.name: frExtCircuitMinBits
frExtCircuitMinBits.description: Minimum number of bits transmitted in Time Period Tc for this PVC.

frExtCircuitMaxBits.name: frExtCircuitMaxBits
frExtCircuitMaxBits.description: Maximum number of bits transmitted in Time Period Tc for this PVC.

frExtCircuitQOctets.name: frExtCircuitQOctets
frExtCircuitQOctets.description: Number of octets queued for transmission because the maximum burst rate was achieved in Tc. These are the number of octets that had transmission delay until next excess burst cycle Tc.

asyncConfigTable.name: asyncConfigTable
asyncConfigTable.description: A table of Async port information.

asyncConfigEntry.name: asyncConfigEntry
asyncConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular async port.

asyncConfigPortIndex.name: asyncConfigPortIndex
asyncConfigPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this port.

asyncConfigType.name: asyncConfigType
asyncConfigType.description: The port type. HASC (Host Async) ports are for attaching to an Async Alarm Central Processor. TASC ports (Terminal Async) ports are for attaching to Alarm Controllers.

asyncNAUName.name: asyncNAUName
asyncNAUName.description: The NAU name of this port. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

asyncInitState.name: asyncInitState
asyncInitState.description: The initial state of the async port. If configured for 'in-service', then the Async port will be brougt up automattically when the unit is powered up. If configured for 'out-of-service', then the Async port must be manually enabled by operator intervention (i.e. enable command must be sent). The default value is 'enabled'.

asyncCarrier.name: asyncCarrier
asyncCarrier.description: This field indicates whether Carrier (a.k.a. CD or DCD, RS-232 pin 8) is constant or switched for DCE devices (internally clocked), or Request To Send (a.k.a. RTS, RS-232 pin 4) is constant or switched. The default value for this parameter is 'constant'.

asyncSpeed.name: asyncSpeed
asyncSpeed.description: The ports speed in bits per second. The default value is 300 bits per second. Speeds higher than 19200 are not supported.

asyncPhysicalType.name: asyncPhysicalType
asyncPhysicalType.description: Physical RS-232 type emulated by the port. The default value is 2 or DCE.

asyncStopBits.name: asyncStopBits
asyncStopBits.description: Number of stop bits generated for transmit characters (received characters may have any number of bits regardless of the configuration). The default value is 1.

asyncParity.name: asyncParity
asyncParity.description: Parity type generated for transmit characters and checked for receive characters. If ODD or EVEN, then if a character is received with invalid parity, it is discarded and the message once completely received is also discarded (i.e. not forwarded to the network). If NONE, then no parity bit is expected within the character or generated to the line. The default value is 1 or NONE.

asyncDataBits.name: asyncDataBits
asyncDataBits.description: Number of data bits (not including the parity bit). The default value is 8.

asyncIdleTimer.name: asyncIdleTimer
asyncIdleTimer.description: The idle timer is amount of time (in milliseconds) used to determine when a complete message has been received from the line. If configured as 0, then this timer is disabled and the message will be sent to the network only when the RX forwarding count is reached. If configured greater than 0, then the timer must be configured for a time longer than the time it takes to receive one character, otherwise the timer will not function properly. The default value is 40.

asyncTxFrameGap.name: asyncTxFrameGap
asyncTxFrameGap.description: The TX frame gap is analogous to the idle timer, but is used to separate messages received from the network by gaps in time so that the Async device can distinguish between multiple messages. If configured as 0, then this function is disabled and if messages are received while transmitting a current message, the the two messages from the network will be sent out with no gap between them. If configured greater than 0, then a gap of the specified number of milliseconds will be inserted. The default value is 40.

asyncRxForwardingCount.name: asyncRxForwardingCount
asyncRxForwardingCount.description: The Async receive forwarding count is used to forward messages when a configured number of characters is received from the Async line. This must be configured to greater than or equal to the maximum message length for a given protocol. The default value is 256.

asyncEiaSignalForwarding.name: asyncEiaSignalForwarding
asyncEiaSignalForwarding.description: The Async EIA signal forwarding is used to cause receive data to be forwarding based on a change of EIA RS-232 control signals. If configured as a DCE, and this field is set ot YES, then if the Request To Send (RTS) control signal (RS-232 DB25 pin 4) changes from active to inactive, any characters already received are forwarded and sent to the network. If configured as a DTE, and this field is set to YES, then if the DCD (Data Carrier Detect) control signal (RS-232 DB25 pin 8) changes from active to inactive, forwarding to the network will occur. The default value is 1 or YES.

asyncAddressOffset.name: asyncAddressOffset
asyncAddressOffset.description: If the address offset is specified as zero, then the data is not parsed to find a device address in order to direct the data to a specified LLC connection. If the address offset is 1 to 255, then the 8 bits specified at that offset (where offset 1 is the first byte of a message received) are interpreted as an address. If this field is set 0 zero, then only one CU record is allowed (i.e. all data sent/received to/from the line is to/from one network connection). If this field is greater than 0 (address offset specified) then one or more CU records can be configured to route the data based on the device address. The default value is 1.

asyncRTC.name: asyncRTC
asyncRTC.description: Defines whether the alarms system protocol has a record termination(forwarding character). The valid range is from hex 01 to hex ff. The default value is not defined.

asyncCTS.name: asyncCTS
asyncCTS.description: Defines whether CTS is an input signal used to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

asyncDCD.name: asyncDCD
asyncDCD.description: Defines whether DCD is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

asyncDSR.name: asyncDSR
asyncDSR.description: Defines whether DSR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DSR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

asyncDTR.name: asyncDTR
asyncDTR.description: Defines whether DTR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and DTR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

asyncRTS.name: asyncRTS
asyncRTS.description: Defines whether RTS is an input signal to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and RTS is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

asyncReturnClock.name: asyncReturnClock
asyncReturnClock.description: Defines whether Return Clock (SCTE) is available as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

asyncOrt.name: asyncOrt
asyncOrt.description: The ORT command is a new port level command. By default, the setting will be YES to set the N2 value to zero, but can be set to NO to indicate that the normal LLC N2 setting should be used. The default value is 'yes'.

asyncStatsEntry.name: asyncStatsEntry
asyncStatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Async port.

asyncStatsPortIndex.name: asyncStatsPortIndex
asyncStatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this Async port.

asyncPortType.name: asyncPortType
asyncPortType.description: The port type. HASC (Host Async) ports are for attaching to an Async Alarm Central Processor. TASC ports (Terminal Async) ports are for attaching to Alarm Controllers.

asyncInMsgDiscarded.name: asyncInMsgDiscarded
asyncInMsgDiscarded.description: The number of received messages discarded.

asyncOutMsgDiscarded.name: asyncOutMsgDiscarded
asyncOutMsgDiscarded.description: The number of sent messages discarded.

asyncXmtFailures.name: asyncXmtFailures
asyncXmtFailures.description: The number of failures in transmission.

asyncRcvMsgForwarded.name: asyncRcvMsgForwarded
asyncRcvMsgForwarded.description: The number of received messages forwarded.

asyncRcvMsgErrors.name: asyncRcvMsgErrors
asyncRcvMsgErrors.description: The number of errors detected in receiving messages.

asyncRcvCharsDiscarded.name: asyncRcvCharsDiscarded
asyncRcvCharsDiscarded.description: The number of received characters discarded.

asyncRcvParityErrors.name: asyncRcvParityErrors
asyncRcvParityErrors.description: The number of parity errors detected.

asyncRcvFramingErrors.name: asyncRcvFramingErrors
asyncRcvFramingErrors.description: The number of errors detected in receiving frames.

bisyncrjeConfigTable.name: bisyncrjeConfigTable
bisyncrjeConfigTable.description: A table of Bisync port information.

bisyncrjeConfigEntry.name: bisyncrjeConfigEntry
bisyncrjeConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Bisync port.

bisyncrjeConfigPortIndex.name: bisyncrjeConfigPortIndex
bisyncrjeConfigPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this port. Current supported Bisync Rje numbers are 1-4.

bisyncrjeConfigType.name: bisyncrjeConfigType
bisyncrjeConfigType.description: The port type. PRJE (Primary RJE) ports emulate a Host and polls the downstream controllers). SRJE ports (Secondary RJE) ports emulate a line with Terminal Controllers (CUs) and respond to polls from the Host.

bisyncrjeNAUName.name: bisyncrjeNAUName
bisyncrjeNAUName.description: The NAU name of this port. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

bisyncrjeInitState.name: bisyncrjeInitState
bisyncrjeInitState.description: The initial state of the Bisync RJE port. If configured for 'in-service', then the Bisync RJE port will be brougt up automattically when the unit is powered up. If configured for 'out-of-service', then the Bisync RJE port must be manually enabled by operator intervention (i.e. enable command must be sent). The default value is 'enabled'.

bisyncrjeCarrier.name: bisyncrjeCarrier
bisyncrjeCarrier.description: This field indicates whether Carrier is constant or switched. The default value for this parameter is 'constant'.

bisyncrjeClocking.name: bisyncrjeClocking
bisyncrjeClocking.description: Clocking source for this port. Setting 'internal' will cause the port to emulate a physical DCE, and setting external will cause the port to emulate a physical DTE. The default value for this field is 'external'.

bisyncrjeSpeed.name: bisyncrjeSpeed
bisyncrjeSpeed.description: The ports speed in bits per second. The default value is 9600 bits per second. Speeds higher than 128000 are not supported.

bisyncrjeReplyTimer.name: bisyncrjeReplyTimer
bisyncrjeReplyTimer.description: The time to wait for a response in seconds. The default value for this field is 3 seconds.

bisyncrjeRetries.name: bisyncrjeRetries
bisyncrjeRetries.description: The maximum number of retries (N2 value) before failing a CU. The default value for this field is 8.

bisyncrjeCodeSet.name: bisyncrjeCodeSet
bisyncrjeCodeSet.description: This parameter sets code set to be used for RJE line. The range of this parameter is ASCII and EBCDIC. The default value for this field is EBCDIC.

bisyncrjeCTS.name: bisyncrjeCTS
bisyncrjeCTS.description: Defines whether CTS is an input signal used to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

bisyncrjeDCD.name: bisyncrjeDCD
bisyncrjeDCD.description: Defines whether DCD is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncrjeDSR.name: bisyncrjeDSR
bisyncrjeDSR.description: Defines whether DSR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DSR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncrjeDTR.name: bisyncrjeDTR
bisyncrjeDTR.description: Defines whether DTR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and DTR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncrjeRTS.name: bisyncrjeRTS
bisyncrjeRTS.description: Defines whether RTS is an input signal to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and RTS is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

bisyncrjeReturnClock.name: bisyncrjeReturnClock
bisyncrjeReturnClock.description: Defines whether Return Clock (SCTE) is available as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

bisyncrjeStatsEntry.name: bisyncrjeStatsEntry
bisyncrjeStatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Bisync port.

bisyncrjeStatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this Bisync RJE port. Current supported numbers are 1-4.

dialbackupConfigTable.name: dialbackupConfigTable
dialbackupConfigTable.description: A table of Sync product dial backup information.

dialbackupConfigEntry.name: dialbackupConfigEntry
dialbackupConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Sync product dial backup port.

dialbackupConfigPortIndex.name: dialbackupConfigPortIndex
dialbackupConfigPortIndex.description: This port uniquely identifies the dial backup port. Range is a valid port number.

dialbackupFirstDedicatedPort.name: dialbackupFirstDedicatedPort
dialbackupFirstDedicatedPort.description: This defines a frame relay PVC which will cause dial backup if it is declared as failed (deactivated) by the network. Port number is a valid Frame Relay and DLCI is a valid Frame Relay DLCI.

dialbackupassociatedDLCIDedicated.name: dialbackupassociatedDLCIDedicated
dialbackupassociatedDLCIDedicated.description: This defines a frame relay PVC which will cause dial backup if it is declared as failed (deactivated) by the network. DLCI is a valid Frame Relay DLCI.

dialbackupSecondDedicatedPort.name: dialbackupSecondDedicatedPort
dialbackupSecondDedicatedPort.description: This defines a second frame relay PVC which will cause dial backup if it is declared as failed (deactivated) by the network. Port number is a valid Frame Relay and DLCI is a valid Frame Relay DLCI.

dialbackupassociatedDLCISecond.name: dialbackupassociatedDLCISecond
dialbackupassociatedDLCISecond.description: This defines a second frame relay PVC which will cause dial backup if it is declared as failed (deactivated) by the network. DLCI is a valid Frame Relay DLCI.

dialbackupDedicatedPort.name: dialbackupDedicatedPort
dialbackupDedicatedPort.description: When this port fails, dial connection is activated. Range is a valid port number. The default value for this field is 1.

dialbackupDedicatedLMIPort.name: dialbackupDedicatedLMIPort
dialbackupDedicatedLMIPort.description: When this port looses LMI connectivity, dial connection is activated. Range is a valid number. The default value for this field is 1.

dialbackupDialInactivityTimer.name: dialbackupDialInactivityTimer
dialbackupDialInactivityTimer.description: This parameter defines inactivity timer for dial connection. Expiration of this timer will cause dial connection to disconnect. The range of this parameter is 0..9999 seconds. Value 0 disables inactivity timer usage. The default value for this field is 60 seconds.

dialbackupDialSuspendTimer.name: dialbackupDialSuspendTimer
dialbackupDialSuspendTimer.description: Defines a duration for which the dial connection. will not be attempted after the dial connection is torn down. The range is 0..9999 seconds. Value of 0 disable inactivity timer usage. The default value for this field is 60 seconds.

dialbackupModemInitString.name: dialbackupModemInitString
dialbackupModemInitString.description: Defins a modem intialization string. The field is 40 characters long. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

dialbackupModemDialString.name: dialbackupModemDialString
dialbackupModemDialString.description: Defins a modem dial string to activate dial connection. This field is up to 40 characters long. Dial phone number may be specified here. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

dialbackupModemHangString.name: dialbackupModemHangString
dialbackupModemHangString.description: Defines a modem hang up string to deactivate dial connection. This field is up to 20 characters long. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

dialbackupDialDelayTimer.name: dialbackupDialDelayTimer
dialbackupDialDelayTimer.description: Defines a duration for which the dial connecton will not be attempted after need to initiate dial connection is detected. The range of this parameter is 0..9999 seconds. Value 0 implies immediate dial initiation. The default value for this field is 60 seconds.

dialbackupTreatLLCControlCharacters.name: dialbackupTreatLLCControlCharacters
dialbackupTreatLLCControlCharacters.description: Defines whether LLC control frames (TEST, XID, RR, RNR, REJ, DISC, UA, DM, FRMR etc. except I frames) are to be considered as user data or not. For a dial backup up port if this contorl frames are not treated as user data, then idle LLC2 sessions on the port will cause inactivity timer to pop causing SNA session disconnect. The range of this parameter is YES or NO. Default value is YES

dialbackupStatsTable.name: dialbackupStatsTable
dialbackupStatsTable.description: A table of Frame Relay information.

dialbackupStatsEntry.name: dialbackupStatsEntry
dialbackupStatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular Frame Relay port.

dialbackupStatsPortIndex.name: dialbackupStatsPortIndex
dialbackupStatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this Dial Backup port.

dialbackupSuccatmpt.name: dialbackupSuccatmpt
dialbackupSuccatmpt.description: The number of successful dial backup attempts.

dialbackupunsuccatmpt.name: dialbackupunsuccatmpt
dialbackupunsuccatmpt.description: The number of unsuccessful dial backup attempts.

dialbackupinact.name: dialbackupinact
dialbackupinact.description: The Number of times inactivity timer expired.

x25ConfigEntry.name: x25ConfigEntry
x25ConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular X25 port.

x25ConfigPortIndex.name: x25ConfigPortIndex
x25ConfigPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this port. Current supported X.25 numbers are 1-4.

x25ConfigType.name: x25ConfigType
x25ConfigType.description: The port type. XDCE () ports is a logical DCE device waits to receive an incoming call from the X.25 network. XDTE ports is a logical DTE device initiates a to the X.25 network. Note that all ports must currently be defined as the same time for a given unit (i.e. no mixing of XDCE and XDTE ports is allowed).

x25NAUName.name: x25NAUName
x25NAUName.description: The NAU name of this port. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

x25InitState.name: x25InitState
x25InitState.description: The initial state of the X.25 port. If configured for 'in-service', then the X.25 port will be brougt up automattically when the unit is powered up. If configured for 'out-of-service', the the X.25 port must be manually enabled by operator intervention (i.e. enable command must be sent). The default value is 'enabled'.

x25Clocking.name: x25Clocking
x25Clocking.description: Clocking source for this port. Setting 'internal' will cause the port to emulate a physical DCE, and setting external will cause the port to emulate a physical DTE. X21 External and Internal are used (with the proper external adapter) to support X.21 Leased Line operation for RS-422/RS-530 (25 pin balanced) interfaces. X21 operation is not supported for boards that operate RS-232 or V.35. The default value for this field is 'external'.

x25DTEAddress.name: x25DTEAddress
x25DTEAddress.description: This parameter specifies the DTE address this port will use to access the X.25 network.

x25LinkWindowSize.name: x25LinkWindowSize
x25LinkWindowSize.description: This parameter sets the maximum number of concurrent unacknowledged I frames at the X.25 data link level. The default value is 7.

x25T1Timer.name: x25T1Timer
x25T1Timer.description: The SDLC T1 timer value in 20ths of a second. The default value is 60 (3 seconds).

x25MaxRetries.name: x25MaxRetries
x25MaxRetries.description: The maximum number of retries (N2 value) before failing a PU. The default value for this field is 8.

x25PortSpeed.name: x25PortSpeed
x25PortSpeed.description: The ports speed in 100 bits per second. The default value is 64000 bits per second. Speeds higher than 19200 are not supported on RS-232 ports units (must be V.35 or RS-422).

x25ReceiveWindowSize.name: x25ReceiveWindowSize
x25ReceiveWindowSize.description: This parameter determines the number of consecutive data packets that the sync unit can receive before requiring an acknowledgment. The default value is 2.

x25TransmitWindowSize.name: x25TransmitWindowSize
x25TransmitWindowSize.description: This parameter determines the number of consecutive data packets to be transmitted on the X.25 network before requiring an acknowledgment. The value you configure in this field must match the value configured in the X.25 network. The default value is 2.

x25ReceivePacketSize.name: x25ReceivePacketSize
x25ReceivePacketSize.description: This parameter defines the size of packets received from the X.25 network in bytes. This value must match the configuration of your X.25 network provider. The default value is 128 bytes.

x25TransmitPacketSize.name: x25TransmitPacketSize
x25TransmitPacketSize.description: This parameter defines the size of packets transmitted across the X.25 network in bytes. This value must match the configuration of the X.25 network. The default value is 128 bytes.

x25LowTwoWayChannel.name: x25LowTwoWayChannel
x25LowTwoWayChannel.description: This parameter specifies the X.25 packet lower-bound channel number for this physical access line. The default value is 1.

x25HighTwoWayChannel.name: x25HighTwoWayChannel
x25HighTwoWayChannel.description: This parameter specifies the X.25 packet upper-bound channel number for this physical access line. Note: This value must be greater than the Low Two-Way Channel Number. The default value is 127.

x25UseCallingAddress.name: x25UseCallingAddress
x25UseCallingAddress.description: This parameter determines whether the DTE Address assigned to the port you are configuring should be included as a calling address in outgoing call packets. The default value is 'No'.

x25ForwardingUnit.name: x25ForwardingUnit
x25ForwardingUnit.description: This parameter limits how many message packets can accumulate before the unit forwards them to higher bytes. The default value is 'EOM'.

x25DevicePacketSize.name: x25DevicePacketSize
x25DevicePacketSize.description: When the sync unit makes a call on behalf of any configured device, the packet size determines parameter negotiation between the calling and the called packet handlers. Note: This parameter is not currently supported. do no change the default value. The default value is 'NONE'.

x25DeviceWindowSize.name: x25DeviceWindowSize
x25DeviceWindowSize.description: When the sync unit makes a call on behalf of any device, the window size determines parameter negotiation between the calling and the called packet handlers. Note: This parameter is not currently supported. do no change the default value. The default value is 'NONE'.

x25PlaceReverseChargeCalls.name: x25PlaceReverseChargeCalls
x25PlaceReverseChargeCalls.description: This parameter determines whether the Sync unit will place reverse charge requests on outgoing calls. The default value is 'No'.

x25AcceptReverseChargeCalls.name: x25AcceptReverseChargeCalls
x25AcceptReverseChargeCalls.description: This parameter determines whether the Sync unit will accept reverse charge requests from incoming calls. The default value is 'No'.

x25NPS.name: x25NPS
x25NPS.description: This parameter indicates if the QLLC conversion NODE is connecting to a NPSI front-end and is to take on a secondary role. The default value is 'No'.

x25CTS.name: x25CTS
x25CTS.description: Defines whether CTS is an input signal used to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

x25DCD.name: x25DCD
x25DCD.description: Defines whether DCD is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

x25DSR.name: x25DSR
x25DSR.description: Defines whether DSR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DSR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

x25DTR.name: x25DTR
x25DTR.description: Defines whether DTR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and DTR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

x25RTS.name: x25RTS
x25RTS.description: Defines whether RTS is an input signal to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and RTS is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

x25ReturnClock.name: x25ReturnClock
x25ReturnClock.description: Defines whether Return Clock (SCTE) is available as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

x25IPAddress.name: x25IPAddress
x25IPAddress.description: This is the IP Address of this interface.

x25NetworkMask.name: x25NetworkMask
x25NetworkMask.description: This is the network mask to be used on this interface.

x25DefaultGatewayAddress.name: x25DefaultGatewayAddress
x25DefaultGatewayAddress.description: Default gateway address to be used when sending responses on this interface.

x25SecondDefaultGatewayAddress.name: x25SecondDefaultGatewayAddress
x25SecondDefaultGatewayAddress.description: Second Default gateway address to be used when sending responses on this interface.

x25StatsEntry.name: x25StatsEntry
x25StatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular X25 port.

x25StatsPortIndex.name: x25StatsPortIndex
x25StatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this X25 port. Current supported numbers on are 1-8.

x25PortType.name: x25PortType
x25PortType.description: The port type. XDCE () ports is a logical DCE device waits to receive an incoming call from the X.25 network. XDTE ports is a logical DTE device initiates a to the X.25 network. Note that all ports must currently be defined as the same time for a given unit (i.e. no mixing of XDCE and XDTE ports is allowed).

x25Sum.name: x25Sum
x25Sum.description: The number of Active Channels Sum.

x25SumsQ.name: x25SumsQ
x25SumsQ.description: The number of Active Channels SumsQ.

x25DataInPkts.name: x25DataInPkts
x25DataInPkts.description: The number of Data Packets received.

x25DataOutPkts.name: x25DataOutPkts
x25DataOutPkts.description: The number of Data Packets sent.

x25DataInChrs.name: x25DataInChrs
x25DataInChrs.description: The number of Data Characters received.

x25DataOutChrs.name: x25DataOutChrs
x25DataOutChrs.description: The number of Data Characters sent.

alcConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular ALC port.

alcConfigPortIndex.name: alcConfigPortIndex
alcConfigPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this port. Current supported X.25 numbers are 1-4.

alcConfigType.name: alcConfigType
alcConfigType.description: The port type. The default is Teminal ALC.

alcNAUName.name: alcNAUName
alcNAUName.description: The NAU name of this port. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

alcInitState.name: alcInitState
alcInitState.description: The initial state of the X.25 port. If configured for 'in-service', then the ALC port will be brougt up automattically when the unit is powered up. If configured for 'out-of-service', the the ALC port must be manually enabled by operator intervention (i.e. enable command must be sent). The default value is 'inservice'.

alcClocking.name: alcClocking
alcClocking.description: Clocking source for this port. Setting 'internal' will cause the port to emulate a physical DCE, and setting external will cause the port to emulate a physical DTE. The default value for this field is 'internal'.

alcPortSpeed.name: alcPortSpeed
alcPortSpeed.description: The ports speed in 100 bits per second. The default value is 9600 bits per second.

alcLimitSegsCharsBetweenPolls.name: alcLimitSegsCharsBetweenPolls
alcLimitSegsCharsBetweenPolls.description: This parameter specifies whether to limit the number of segments sent between pools. If this parameter is set to 'yes' the parameter 'Number of Segments' and 'Number of Characters' should be configured appropriately. The defualt value is 'yes'.

alcNumberOfSegments.name: alcNumberOfSegments
alcNumberOfSegments.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of segments that may be sent between polls. This parameter is applicable only if 'Limit SEGs/Chars between polls' is set to yes. The defualt value is 5.

alcNumberOfCharacters.name: alcNumberOfCharacters
alcNumberOfCharacters.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of characters that may be sent between polls. This parameter is applicable only if 'Limit SEGs/Chars between polls' is set to yes. The defualt value is 2000.

alcNumberOfNullSeg.name: alcNumberOfNullSeg
alcNumberOfNullSeg.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of null characters that may be sent between segments. The defualt value is 0.

alcCTS.name: alcCTS
alcCTS.description: Defines whether CTS is an input signal used to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

alcDCD.name: alcDCD
alcDCD.description: Defines whether DCD is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DCD is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

alcDSR.name: alcDSR
alcDSR.description: Defines whether DSR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to external. For internal clocking the parameter is ignored and DSR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

alcDTR.name: alcDTR
alcDTR.description: Defines whether DTR is required as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and DTR is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

alcRTS.name: alcRTS
alcRTS.description: Defines whether RTS is an input signal to determine the port status. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored and RTS is asserted when port is enabled. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'No'.

alcReturnClock.name: alcReturnClock
alcReturnClock.description: Defines whether Return Clock (SCTE) is available as input signal or ignored. This parameter is applicable if the clocking is set to internal. For external clocking the parameter is ignored. The range is yes and no. The default value is 'yes'.

alcStatsEntry.name: alcStatsEntry
alcStatsEntry.description: An entry consisting of port information for a particular X25 port.

alcStatsPortIndex.name: alcStatsPortIndex
alcStatsPortIndex.description: The port number that uniquely identifies this Alc port. Current supported numbers on are 1-8.

alcPortType.name: alcPortType
alcPortType.description: The port type. The default is Terminal Alc.

alcSegRxDisc.name: alcSegRxDisc
alcSegRxDisc.description: The number of Received Segments Discarded.

alcSegTxDisc.name: alcSegTxDisc
alcSegTxDisc.description: The number of Transmitted Segments Discarded.

puControlTable.name: puControlTable
puControlTable.description: A table for controlling lines and obtaining information.

puControlEntry.name: puControlEntry
puControlEntry.description: An entry consisting of PU information for a particular port.

puControlLineIndex.name: puControlLineIndex
puControlLineIndex.description: The port number that has a given PU.

puControlPUAddress.name: puControlPUAddress
puControlPUAddress.description: The PU address in the range of 0x01 to 0xfe.

puStatus.name: puStatus
puStatus.description: The status of the PU. To change status of a port an enable, enable all or disable may be set. Valid Return status are enable(d), disable(d), or failed. Commands: An enable command will attempt to bring up the PU. An enable all command will attempt to bring up the line and any lower layer entities (e.g. PUs). A disable command will disable the PU. Status: Enable(d) indicates the PU is enabled and running. Disable(d) indicates the PU has been disabled. Failed indicates the PU is enabled and not Running. For a access LAN/X25 PU, the status is enabled when the connection status is connected. Otherwise its status is failed.

puConnectionStatus.name: puConnectionStatus
puConnectionStatus.description: The status of the LLC type 2 Connection for this SDLC PU.

puLastClearCode.name: puLastClearCode
puLastClearCode.description: A two octet field indicating the Last Clearing Cause and Diagnostic Field of the last failed connection attempt (a.k.a. call attempt) or active connection (a.k.a. session). For LLC type 2 connections the second octet (cause) is always 0. The first octet (diagnostic) indicates the reason for the last connection failure. A value of 255 (xff) indicates that no call has ever been placed (e.g. PU never came up) or received. Even if the session call attempt is successful, the first octect still indicates the reason of LAST TIME when the session call attempt failed. See User's Guide for information

puControlFailureCode.name: puControlFailureCode
puControlFailureCode.description: This entry contains the failure codes if the associated PU is in the failed state.

puControlNAUName.name: puControlNAUName
puControlNAUName.description: The NAU name of this PU. The default value for this field is all blank (filled with ASCII space 0x20 characters).

puConnectionAttemptCount.name: puConnectionAttemptCount
puConnectionAttemptCount.description: The number of connection attempts performed. This count is set to zero at startup, and after every loss of an estabished session.

puStatusIgnored.name: puStatusIgnored
puStatusIgnored.description: This field is used for consolidating status of the unit. The status of this pu is not put into consideration when consolidating status of the unit if this field is set to yes.

puStatusAcknowledged.name: puStatusAcknowledged
puStatusAcknowledged.description: This field is used for consolidating status of the unit. When this field is set to yes, the unit will re-consolidate its status without putting the status of this pu into consideration. Subseqent status change of the pu will cause the unit to include it in computing the status of the unit. Setting this value to no has no effect.

puLastDlciCleared.name: puLastDlciCleared
puLastDlciCleared.description: Specifies the dlci that the last clear code was associated with. If the last clear code was not associated with a virtual route, i.e. the clear was associated with the lan for example, this field is set to 9999.

puCurrentDlci.name: puCurrentDlci
puCurrentDlci.description: Specifies the DLCI active for a session at this time. For LAN or X25 network interface, this field is set to 0

puLastMACCleared.name: puLastMACCleared
puLastMACCleared.description: Specifies the MAC address that the last clear code was associated with.

puCurrentMAC.name: puCurrentMAC
puCurrentMAC.description: Specifies the MAC address that the current session is associated with. For X25 network type, this is set to 0.

puNetworkType.name: puNetworkType
puNetworkType.description: Specifies netowrk type that the current session is associated with.

puCurrentConnectionType.name: puCurrentConnectionType
puCurrentConnectionType.description: Specifies network layer that the current session is associated with.

puLastSVCCleared.name: puLastSVCCleared
puLastSVCCleared.description: Specifies the LCN that the last clear code is associated with. If the last clear code was not associated with a X25 SVC, i.e. the clear was associated with the lan for example, this field is set to 9999.

puCurrentSVC.name: puCurrentSVC
puCurrentSVC.description: Specifies the that the current session is associated with. For non X25 network type, this field is set to 0

puLastLocalDTECleared.name: puLastLocalDTECleared
puLastLocalDTECleared.description: Specifies the local DTE address that the last clear code is associated with. For non X25 network type, this field is set to 0

puLastRemoteDTECleared.name: puLastRemoteDTECleared
puLastRemoteDTECleared.description: Specifies the remote DTE address that the last clear code is associated with. For non X25 network type, this field is set to 0

puCurrentLocalDTE.name: puCurrentLocalDTE
puCurrentLocalDTE.description: Specifies the local DTE address that the current session is associated with. For non X25 network type, this field is set to 0

puCurrentRemoteDTE.name: puCurrentRemoteDTE
puCurrentRemoteDTE.description: Specifies the remote DTE address that the current session is associated with. For non X25 network type, this field is set to 0

puIsDynamic.name: puIsDynamic

mappingPuConfigEntry.name: mappingPuConfigEntry
mappingPuConfigEntry.description: This field is obsolete. This entry contains information about a given mapping PU. Each entry includes MAC/SAP information for a source PU and a similar information for the partner (mapped) PU. Depending upon whether the PU is LAN-attached, SDLC-attached or Frame Relay-attached, one or more fields may not apply. Some fields, for example, mappingPuNAU, mappingPuXID, mappingPuConnectID are common to both end points. The entry is indexed by the port number and the PU number.

mappingPuConfigLineIndex.name: mappingPuConfigLineIndex
mappingPuConfigLineIndex.description: This field is obsolete. The port number for which PU is associated with. Port number 99 is a special value which is used to indicate NetView PU.

mappingPuConfigAddress.name: mappingPuConfigAddress
mappingPuConfigAddress.description: This field is obsolete. The PU address in the range of 0x01 to 0xfe.

mappingPuSourceSAP.name: mappingPuSourceSAP
mappingPuSourceSAP.description: This field is obsolete. The LLC source SAP value for this PU. Typically the source SAP will vary for each PU. This is due to the fact that most Sync products are configured to always call the same remote Token-Ring Host or Gateway for all connections configured. This means that all the Destination SAP (usually set to 4) and Destination MAC addresses are the same, so the Source SAP field must be set to a unique value in order to uniquely identify the LLC connection to the Host. (SNA does not allow multiplexing of PUs on one LLC connection. Each PU must have its own LLC Type 2 connection.) This field must be set to a range between 04 and E8 hexadecimal and it must be evenly divisible by 4 (802.2 LLC rules for user assigned SAPs). This field is not applicable in all cases, if not it returns a dummy value. This parameter defaults to a value of 4.

mappingPuDestinationSAP.name: mappingPuDestinationSAP
mappingPuDestinationSAP.description: This field is obsolete. The LLC Destination SAP value for this PU. For SNA typically the destination is almost always SAP 4. However both Host Front Ends (e.g. 3745) or Gateways (e.g. 3174) allow SAPs to be configured for any value betwee 0x04 and 0xEC as long as the SAP ID is a user assignable individual SAP ID (any value evenly divisable by 4). This field is not applicable to all cases. If not it returns a dummy value. This parameter defaults to a value of 4.

mappingPuDestinationMAC.name: mappingPuDestinationMAC
mappingPuDestinationMAC.description: This field is obsolete. The LAN Destination MAC address used in the LLC Type 2 connection for this PU. The Token-Ring format for this field is a 6 octet (48 bit) field represented in IEEE 802.5 format where the first bit transmitted is the most significant bit. The destination MAC must also be an 'Individual' address. Therefore valid addresses are between 000000000001 and 7FFFFFFFFFFF (an address of all zeroes is not supported). The Ethernet format for this field is a 6 octet (48 bit) field represented in IEEE 802.3 format where the first bit transmitted is the least significant bit. The destination MAC must also be an 'Individual' address. Therefore valid addresses must start with the least significant bit equal to 0. In other words, the first two digits must be in the set of 0x00, 0x02, 0x04, ... 0xFE (an address of all 12 digits equal to zeroes is not supported). This field is not applicable to all cases. If not it returns a dummy value.

mappingPuPartnerConfigLineIndex.name: mappingPuPartnerConfigLineIndex
mappingPuPartnerConfigLineIndex.description: This field is obsolete. The port number for the partner PU associated with source PU. Port number 99 is a special value which is used to indicate NetView PU.

mappingPuPartnerConfigAddress.name: mappingPuPartnerConfigAddress
mappingPuPartnerConfigAddress.description: This field is obsolete. The PU address of the partner PU in the range of 0x01 to 0xfe.

mappingPuPartnerSourceSAP.name: mappingPuPartnerSourceSAP
mappingPuPartnerSourceSAP.description: This field is obsolete. The LLC source SAP value for a partner PU. Typically the source SAP will vary for each PU. mappingPuPartnerDestSAP.name: mappingPuPartnerDestSAP
mappingPuPartnerDestSAP.description: This field is obsolete. The LLC Destination SAP value for the partner PU. For SNA typically the destination is almost always SAP 4. This field is not applicable to all cases. It returns a dummy value. This parameter defaults to a value of 4.

mappingPuPartnerDestMAC.name: mappingPuPartnerDestMAC
mappingPuPartnerDestMAC.description: This field is obsolete. The LAN Destination MAC address used in the LLC Type 2 connection for the partner PU. The Token-Ring format for this field is a 6 octet (48 bit) field represented in IEEE 802.5 format where the first bit transmitted is the most significant bit. The destination MAC must also be an 'Individual' address. Therefore valid addresses are between 000000000001 and 7FFFFFFFFFFF (an address of all zeroes is not supported). The Ethernet format for this field is a 6 octet (48 bit) field represented in IEEE 802.3 format where the first bit transmitted is the least significant bit. The destination MAC must also be an 'Individual' address. Therefore valid addresses must start with the least significant bit equal to 0. In other words, the first two digits must be in the set of 0x00, 0x02, 0x04, ... 0xFE (an address of all 12 digits equal to zeroes is not supported). This field is not applicable to all cases. If not it returns a dummy value.

mappingPuNAU.name: mappingPuNAU
mappingPuNAU.description: This field is obsolete. The NAU Name. The NAU name is same for both the source PU and the partner PU. It represents one physical PU in a network.

mappingPuConnectID.name: mappingPuConnectID
mappingPuConnectID.description: This field is obsolete. The connection ID. This must match a connection ID of an access line PU or another mapping PU Connection ID. The connnection ID is 0 if there is no mapping.

mappingPuXID.name: mappingPuXID
mappingPuXID.description: This field is obsolete. The XID value for this PU. The XID is used to identify the PU during the LLC connection process to the remote Host or Gateway. For incoming LLC connections on Sync Research products this field is parsed to route the connection to the proper PU. The XID is same for both the source PU and the partner PU. It represents one physical PU in a network. The default value for this field is all zeroes.

mappingPuDirectDLCI.name: mappingPuDirectDLCI
mappingPuDirectDLCI.description: This field is obsolete. The Frame Relay DLCI used in the LLC Type 2 connection for this PU. The Frame Relay format for this field is a 2 octet (16 bit) field represented in BCD format. A valid DLCI would be from 0001 to 1023 (0000 is reserved for AnnexD management. 1023 is reserved for LMI mangement.). This value is applicable to Frame Relay-attached PU only. The field corresponds to a source port or a partner port depending upon whether the source PU is a Frame Relay-attached PU or the partner PU is Frame Relay-attached PU. For Frame Relay-attached PU if this value is not configured, 0 is returned.

mappingPuLastClearCode.name: mappingPuLastClearCode
mappingPuLastClearCode.description: This field is obsolete. A two octet field indicating the Last Clearing Cause and Diagnostic Field of the last failed connection attempt (a.k.a. call attempt) or active connection (a.k.a. session) for this PU. For LLC type 2 connections the first octet (cause) is always 0. The second octet (diagnostic) indicates the reason for the last connection failure. The second octet is set to 0 when a sucessful call has been placed, or if no call has ever been placed, or the clear is initiated by the partner for which mappingPuPartnerLastClearCode has the clear code. If the second octet is non-zero then it indicates the reason for the connection attempt failure. See User's Guide for more information

mappingPuConnAttemptCnt.name: mappingPuConnAttemptCnt
mappingPuConnAttemptCnt.description: This field is obsolete. The number of connection attempts performed for this PU. This count is set to zero at startup, and after every loss of an estabished session.
